OL,3,CMother's son, 9, developed eating
OL,4,Cdisorder after infected water crisis
OL,6,F"We weren't ultimately allowed out of
OL,7,Fthe hospital until he had reluctantly
OL,8,Fagreed to tolerate some meal
OL,9,Freplacement drinks. A year on and he's
OL,10,Fstill completely reliant upon them. He
OL,11,Fhasn't eaten a meal since before 7 May
OL,12,Flast year."
OL,14,F'It changed me, mummy'
OL,16,FJen's son, who is also autistic, was
OL,17,Flater diagnosed with a serious
OL,18,Fcondition known as Arfid - which
OL,19,Fstands for Avoidant/restrictive food
OL,20,Fintake disorder.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
