OL,3,CMother's son, 9, developed eating
OL,4,Cdisorder after infected water crisis
OL,6,F"As a mum, it's heartbreaking to see
OL,7,Fyour child go through this, to see
OL,8,Fthem scared of eating and drinking -
OL,9,Fthe things that as humans, we need to
OL,10,Fsurvive. And he's scared of doing
OL,11,Fthat."
OL,13,F'It's unforgivable'
OL,15,FSouth West Water has apologised for
OL,16,Fthe crisis and promised it will not
OL,17,Fhappen again.
OL,19,FJen says the company's approach last
OL,20,Fsummer was "abysmal".
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
